externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthPo.name: externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthPool
externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthPo.description: If TRUE an IP address is allocated from the default pool and passed to the RADIUS server during RADIUS authentication. This address may be assigned to the dial-in user for the duration of the connection.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthTi.name: externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthTimeout
externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthTi.description: Number of seconds between retries to the authentication host.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthRs.name: externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthRspRequired
externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthRs.description: When set to Yes, entry is allowed only if the authentication server responds with an authentication of the login information. When set to No, entry is also allowed if there is no response from the authentication server. This field is used only for CLID or DNIS authentication.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthId.name: externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthIdFailReturnBusy
externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthId.description: Return busy instead of normal call clearing when id authentication fails.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthId.name: externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthIdTimeoutReturnBusy
externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthId.description: Return busy instead of normal call clearing when external id authentication fails.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthId.description: Maximum time limit to spend retrying RADIUS servers when in id authentication, a value of 0 sets the limit to the internal default value.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_IdAuth.name: externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_IdAuthPrefix
externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_IdAuth.description: A short text string prepended to the username portion of a CLID or DNIS authentication request.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AllowU.description: When set to 'YES', unencrypted as well as encrypted Tunnel-Password, from RADIUS, is accepted. When set to 'NO' only encrypted Tunnel-Password, from RADIUS, is accepted. But as per RFC 2868 the Tunnel-Password MUST be encrypted by RADIUS before sending out.

externalAuthProfile_RadAuthClient_AuthCl.description: Pseudo DNIS number for CLI users. If set, this number is sent to RADIUS as DNIS. If not set, DNIS is not sent to RADIUS.
